---
import Layout from '../shared/layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../shared/components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../shared/components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="About Us & Our Engineering Philosophy" 
  description="Kroma AI Systems Inc. and the KASI brand: Discover our development philosophy, the Vancouver Matrix, and our commitment to clean architecture."
>
  <Navbar />

  <!-- Institutional Hero -->
  <section class="about-hero">
    <div class="glow-blur glow-blue" style="top: 20%; left: -5%;"></div>
    <div class="container hero-container-compact">
      <span class="badge">About KASI</span>
      <h1>Technical pragmatism & structural <span class="text-gradient">integrity</span></h1>
      <p class="large">
        We were born in Vancouver, BC, under a simple premise: unnecessary complexity in software is the worst enemy of business profitability.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Narrative Section (6/6 Grid) -->
  <section class="narrative-section">
    <div class="container grid-12 narrative-grid">
      <!-- Left: Corporate Vision (6 cols) -->
      <div class="narrative-left">
        <span class="badge">Our Mission</span>
        <h2>The vision of Kroma AI Systems Inc.</h2>
        <p>
          Modern organizations often suffer from poorly designed systems that break silently under minor external changes. At Kroma AI Systems Inc., we focus on engineering resilient architectures and autonomous self-healing pipelines.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not believe in endless specifications or bloated deadlines. We believe in functional incremental deliveries, highly testable and decoupled code, and the strategic use of Artificial Intelligence to accelerate your business capabilities.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: Narrative and Vancouver Matrix (6 cols) -->
      <div class="narrative-right">
        <div class="matrix-card">
          <span class="matrix-tag">Geographical & Cultural Context</span>
          <h3>The Vancouver Matrix</h3>
          <p>
            We operate from the technology hub of British Columbia, Canada, an environment deeply influenced by West Coast trade flows and two major multicultural pillars: South Asian and East Asian.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our visual and strategic identity stems from this local and global duality, channeling a silent message of trust, solidity, and connectivity into every system we build.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Visual Emblem Breakdown: Dual-Layer Identity -->
  <section class="emblem-section">
    <div class="glow-blur glow-cyan" style="bottom: 10%; right: 10%;"></div>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="badge">Our Brand</span>
        <h2>Symbolic Fusion & Identity Philosophy</h2>
        <p>
          KASI is not just a brand; it is a manifesto of technical realism and cultural alignment.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="emblem-grid grid-12">
        <div class="emblem-card left-card">
          <span class="emblem-tag">Layer A: Semantic Irony</span>
          <h3>"KASI" as Practical Realism</h3>
          <p class="irony-desc">
            In Spanish, KASI sounds exactly like <em>"casi"</em> (almost). Instead of hiding this, we weaponized it as our greatest strength:
          </p>
          <div class="irony-box">
            <span class="quote">"We are not perfect, but we KASI always deliver."</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            It acknowledges that in real-world engineering, there are no magical, bulletproof systems; there are only senior teams capable of anticipating failures and programming systems that self-recover under any adversity.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="emblem-card right-card">
          <span class="emblem-tag">Layer B: Cultural Shield</span>
          <h3>Encrypted Symbols of Trust</h3>
          <p>
            The geometric design of our logo (available in our local brand kits) fuses three key concepts for Vancouver's commercial engine:
          </p>
          <ul class="emblem-bullets">
            <li>
              <strong>South Asian Resonance (Punjabi/Sikh):</strong> Traces lines evoking the sacred geometry of <em>Ek Onkar</em> (ੴ), conveying absolute moral integrity and reliability.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>East Asian Core (Chinese 卡 - Kǎ):</strong> Internal structure inspired by the Chinese ideogram for "card" or "integrated circuit", representing technological foundations.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>The Silk Network (Chinese 丝 - Sī):</strong> Flowing strokes simulating silk threads, representing connection networks and continuous data pipelines.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <div class="brand-kits-images">
            <img src="/assets/logos/logo_varians.png" alt="KASI Brand Variations" class="about-brand-img" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Technical Timeline -->
  <section class="timeline-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="badge">Evolution</span>
        <h2>Our Technical Trajectory</h2>
        <p>From a local software architecture studio to processing millions of daily data transactions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-badge">2023</div>
          <div class="timeline-panel">
            <h4>Founding of Kroma AI Systems Inc.</h4>
            <p>Legal registration in British Columbia, Canada, providing software architecture services for logistics operators.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-badge">2024</div>
          <div class="timeline-panel">
            <h4>Birth of the Resilient Scraping Engine</h4>
            <p>Development and internal release of advanced crawlers capable of dynamic CAPTCHA bypass and autonomous proxy control.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-badge">2025</div>
          <div class="timeline-panel">
            <h4>On-Premises Local LLMs Integration</h4>
            <p>Successful deployment of local Llama-3 models for automated processing of manifests and commercial port cargo.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-badge">2026</div>
          <div class="timeline-panel">
            <h4>KASI Global Launch</h4>
            <p>Integration of capabilities under the KASI acronym, designing and hardening critical pipelines for clients across North America.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Core Values -->
  <section class="values-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="badge">Our Values</span>
        <h2>Rigid Engineering Pillars</h2>
        <p>Principles that define how we write code and how we engage with your business.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="values-grid grid-12">
        <div class="card value-card">
          <div class="val-num">I</div>
          <h3>Technical Precision</h3>
          <p>We avoid rough estimates. Every variable, pipeline, and service is strictly typed and thoroughly documented.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card value-card">
          <div class="val-num">II</div>
          <h3>Data Resiliency</h3>
          <p>We assume that networks will fail, external APIs will change, and servers will crash. We design to endure.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card value-card">
          <div class="val-num">III</div>
          <h3>Clean Architecture</h3>
          <p>We keep business logic isolated from physical dependencies. Readable code that survives technological shifts.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card value-card">
          <div class="val-num">IV</div>
          <h3>Total Automation</h3>
          <p>If a technical task must be performed more than three times, it is a mandatory candidate for a secure, scheduled script.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Hero */
  .about-hero {
    padding-top: calc(var(--space-12) + 40px);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-6);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hero-container-compact {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  /* Narrative Grid (6/6) */
  .narrative-grid {
    align-items: center;
    gap: 32px;
  }

  .narrative-left {
    grid-column: 1 / 7;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .narrative-right {
    grid-column: 7 / 13;
  }

  .matrix-card {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(0, 157, 255, 0.08), rgba(0, 200, 255, 0.03));
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 157, 255, 0.2);
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: var(--space-6);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .matrix-tag {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-cyan-accent);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  /* Emblem Section */
  .emblem-section {
    background: rgba(2, 11, 24, 0.5);
    border-block: 1px solid rgba(230, 231, 234, 0.08);
  }

  .emblem-grid {
    gap: 32px;
  }

  .emblem-card {
    grid-column: span 6;
    background: var(--grad-dark-card);
    border: 1px solid rgba(230, 231, 234, 0.1);
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: var(--space-6);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .emblem-tag {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-electric-blue);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .emblem-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  .irony-desc {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-silver-dark);
  }

  .irony-box {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-cyan-accent);
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
  }

  .irony-box .quote {
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-white);
  }

  .emblem-bullets {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .emblem-bullets li {
    font-family: var(--font-secondary);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    position: relative;
    padding-left: var(--space-4);
  }

  .emblem-bullets li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 10px;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--color-electric-blue);
  }

  .brand-kits-images {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    border-radius: 10px;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid rgba(230, 231, 234, 0.1);
  }

  .about-brand-img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }

  /* Timeline */
  .timeline {
    position: relative;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-block: var(--space-5);
  }

  /* Line running through center */
  .timeline::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 50%;
    top: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 2px;
    background: rgba(230, 231, 234, 0.1);
    transform: translateX(-50%);
  }

  .timeline-item {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    width: 50%;
    padding-right: var(--space-6);
  }

  /* Every second item goes right */
  .timeline-item:nth-child(even) {
    align-self: flex-end;
    justify-content: flex-start;
    margin-left: 50%;
    padding-right: 0;
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
  }

  .timeline-badge {
    position: absolute;
    right: -25px;
    top: 15px;
    background: var(--color-primary-navy);
    border: 2px solid var(--color-electric-blue);
    color: var(--color-cyan-accent);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    width: 50px;
    height: 50px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    z-index: 10;
  }

  .timeline-item:nth-child(even) .timeline-badge {
    left: -25px;
    right: auto;
  }

  .timeline-panel {
    background: var(--grad-dark-card);
    border: 1px solid rgba(230, 231, 234, 0.08);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: var(--space-5);
    width: 100%;
    box-shadow: 0 10px 25px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
  }

  .timeline-panel h4 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
  }

  .timeline-panel p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* Values Section */
  .values-grid {
    gap: 24px;
  }

  .value-card {
    grid-column: span 3;
    padding: var(--space-6);
    min-height: 280px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .val-num {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: rgba(0, 157, 255, 0.3);
    font-family: var(--font-primary);
  }

  .value-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  .value-card p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* Responsive Design */
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .narrative-left {
      grid-column: span 12;
      margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    }

    .narrative-right {
      grid-column: span 12;
    }

    .emblem-card {
      grid-column: span 12;
    }

    .timeline::before {
      left: 20px;
    }

    .timeline-item {
      width: 100%;
      padding-left: var(--space-6) !important;
      padding-right: 0 !important;
      margin-left: 0 !important;
      justify-content: flex-start;
    }

    .timeline-badge {
      left: -5px !important;
      right: auto !important;
    }

    .value-card {
      grid-column: span 6;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .value-card {
      grid-column: span 12;
      min-height: auto;
    }
  }
</style>
